e indicator injection. ConclusionS: Cardiac output measurement by ultrasound dilution does not cause clinically relevant changes in cerebral and systemic circulation and oxygenation in a piglet model. Copyright {\textcopyright} 2010 by the Society of Critical Care Medicine and the World Federation of Pediatric Intensive and Critical Care Societies.},
